{"name":"Character Creation","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Character Creation</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<h2>Campaign Intention</h2>\n<p>We are embarking on a pirate campaign. This is intended to be very pulpy and swashbuckling in nature. So this campaign will need characters that are interested in acquiring fame and/or welath through piracy. This will be a sand box campaign style driven by players. The party will determine the kind of pirates you are. Are you ruthless cutthroats? Are you pirates that have a code of honor? Are there only particular targets you go after? Is everything a target? Do you raid villages? If so, whose? Or do you just stick to the high seas? Do you ruthlessly press-gang locals or sailors to fill the ranks of your ship? Or do you only hire those who want to come on board?</p>\n<p>While there is no expectation for the characters to be ruthless pirates, it is still expected that you will be committing acts of piracy against <em><strong>someone</strong></em><em> </em>or <em><strong>some group</strong></em><em>. </em>Characters are not expected to be evil, however this is one campaign that moral lines can be blurred. Greed is expected. Ruthlessness, while not necessary, is a quality that will fit in the campaign. Characters that want to plunder sea lanes <em>for some reason</em> are going to be needed for this camapign.</p>\n<h2>Setting Rules for Character Creation</h2>\n<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-abfd1f68-7fff-b336-75bd-3c1f84cb93be\" dir=\"ltr\">These are the following setting rules we will use. I am open to using others if you want.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Born A Hero]{Born A Hero}:</strong> Player characters ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} requirements for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Born from War]{Born from War}:</strong> Player characters start with a free @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Edges]{Background Edge} that must be tied to their backstory experiences during the Last War during @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Character Creation Summary]{character creation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Creative Combat]{Creative Combat}:</strong> A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} allows the character to roll on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Creative Combat]{special table} that grants additional effects.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dynamic Backlash]{Dynamic Backlash}:</strong> A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane} skill roll forces the player to roll on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dynamic Backlash]{special table} with various chaotic results.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fanatics]{Fanatics}:</strong> Enemy thugs take the damage for their masters.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Glory and Infamy]{Glory and Infamy}:</strong> Glory or Infamy track the reputation of the Player Characters. As it increases they are awarded with benefits from those that respect the reputation of the character.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.More Skill Points]{More Skill Points}:</strong> Player characters in advanced or specialized settings start with 15 skill points.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmored Hero]{Unarmored Hero}:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} without armor add +2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} rolls.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kum3o0fx46","path":"Pirates of Cyre","color":"#008000"}},"_id":"oT73BBgLFzeCiP9q"}
{"name":"Player World Development","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Player World Development</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<h2>Campaign Intention</h2>\n<p>We are embarking on a pirate campaign. This is intended to be very pulpy and swashbuckling in nature. So this campaign will need characters that are interested in acquiring fame and/or welath through piracy. This will be a sand box campaign style driven by players. The party will determine the kind of pirates you are. Are you ruthless cutthroats? Are you pirates that have a code of honor? Are there only particular targets you go after? Is everything a target? Do you raid villages? If so, whose? Or do you just stick to the high seas? Do you ruthlessly press-gang locals or sailors to fill the ranks of your ship? Or do you only hire those who want to come on board?</p>\n<p>While there is no expectation for the characters to be ruthless pirates, it is still expected that you will be committing acts of piracy against <em><strong>someone</strong></em><em> </em>or <em><strong>some group</strong></em><em>. </em>Characters are not expected to be evil, however this is one campaign that moral lines can be blurred. Greed is expected. Ruthlessness, while not necessary, is a quality that will fit in the campaign. Characters that want to plunder sea lanes <em>for some reason</em> are going to be needed for this camapign.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kum3o0fx46","path":"Pirates of Cyre","color":"#008000"}},"_id":"dUAccHrWHZYDkKUE"}
{"name":"Plot Point Campaign","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Plot Point Campaign</h1>\n</div>\n<h2>Plot Points</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Port Verge, Press-Ganged and Keelhauling:</strong> The scoundrals start with an evening in Port Verge. Wake up press ganged in the Wormwood. Are assigned roles, and then watch a good keelhauling. <em>Day 1 from The Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Day in the life of a pirate: </strong>The scoundrals are bullied by some crew sent my Master Scourge. A few days later they are sent to deal with the bilges. A brawl with owlbear. <em>Day 2, Day4, and Day 5 from The Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Storm at Sea:</strong> The scoundrals have to survive a storm at sea on the Wormwood. <em>Day 8 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Pirate Duties:</strong> The scoundrals have a few series of encounters. Gathering some crabs for the captain. Training for boarding. Unpleasant duties and attack in the bilges. <em>Day 11, day 14, Day 17, and Day 19 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Man's Promise:</strong> The crew of the Wormwood attacks and takes over the Man's Promise. The scoundrals are assigned to the skeleton crew. <em>Day 20 and 21 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Whisper's of Mutiny:</strong> Things go grim for the Man's Promise crew. The ship is caught in a Storm and shipwrecked. <em>Day 1 to 5 from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Bonewrack Isle:</strong> Exploring Bonewrack Isle and rescue crew members from the grindylows. <em>Bonewrack Isle from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Mutiny!:</strong> The scoundrals mutiny against Mister Dabrak and take over the Man's Promise. <em>Mutiny from the Wormwood Mutiny</em></li>\n<li><strong>Hiding the Evidence!:</strong> The scoundrals take the Man's Promise to Rickety' Squibs to disguise their ship and recristen it. <em>Hiding the Evidence from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Landlubber Trap:</strong> The scoundrals encounter a ship that has been set as a trap by Sauaghin. <em>Event 11: Hook, Line, and Sinkerfrom Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Cracking Tidewater Rock:</strong> The scoundrals find a base of operations by gaining control of Tidewater Rock. <em>Tidewater Rock from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Raid on the Rock:</strong> (Required Landlubber Trap) The scoundrals find a base of operations by gaining control of Tidewater Rock. (perhaps use Attack on Brigandy Bay pg 147 for some ideas on how to conduct the fight) <em>Combined Event 16 and 17 from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Treasure Hunting in Mancatching Cove:</strong> The scoundrals sail to mancatcher cove and battle the Sahuaghin there to gain the treasure that has been left there. <em>The Treasure of Mancatacher Cove from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Savage Tales</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sea Wolves:</strong> The scoundrals commit an act of priacy on the hazaar Seas. <em>Event 7 from Piracy on the fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Raiding Settlements:</strong> The scoundrals may commit land raids on sea-side settlements. <em>Event 8: Low-Hanging Fruit from Piracy on the fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Upon the Famished Mane:</strong> The scoundrals encounter a pirate ship being burned by a Karrnathi warship. <em>Event 10: Upon the Famished Mane from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>No Honor Among Thieves:</strong> This savage tale occurs as the scoundrals come upon an attack by another pirate ship already underway. The PCs first sight the battle from a mile away and come upon it just as the pirates have disabled the merchant ship and now prepare to board her. <em>Event 13: No Honor Among Thieves from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Frying Pan:</strong> The scoundrals encounter a Karrn or Brelish pirate hunter. <em>Event 13: The Frying Pan from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>For Whom the Bell Tolls:</strong> This savage tale takes place over three successive nights when the scoundrals are out of sight of the nearest shore. It always occurs in the waning hours of the day as the sun sinks below the horizon, as they are stalked and attacked by a ghost ship. <em>Event 14: For Whom the Bell Tolls from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Hijack the Immortal:</strong> The scoundrals are highered by someone to hijack a powerful warship. <em>Hijack the Immortal pg 140 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Debauchery:</strong> The scoundrals are approached by a vengeful father to assassinate someone who has defiled his daughter. <em>Debauchery pg 141 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Terror:</strong> Can the scoundrals rescue a unwilling shipwright from service on Prince Rhygers secret vessel. <em>The Terror pg 151 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Treasure for the Taking:</strong> The scoundrals are lead to some buried treasure by Stumpy Pete (Stumpy Pete perhaps works at Rickety Squibs). <em>Treasure for the Taking pg 154 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Low Down:</strong> The scoundrals find a dinghy at seas, they rescue one of the most ruthless pirates in the Lhazaar Seas. <em>The Low Down pg 156 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Butcher:</strong> (Requires The Low Down) The scoundrals find a ship with sailors horribly butchered. If they set off in persuit they find the man they rescued. What will the scoundrals do? <em>The Butcher pg 156 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Big for Freedom:</strong> The scoundrals are asked to save a salve girl serving at a tavern in a port town? <em>Bid for Freedom pg 160 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>Revenge:</strong> (Could be used to turn against the Seadragons??) When the scoundrals try to sell some treasure, and item is noticed by a heartbroken lover. He asks for help with revenge? <em>Revenge pg 173 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Dragonshard Ship:</strong> The scoundrals are asked to help a fellow pirate with some piracy, but find it better guarded than thought. <em>The Iron Ship pg 173 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>False Kidnapping:</strong> The scoundrals are asked by a noble to stage a fake kidnapping. <em>False Kidnapping pg 176 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>The Black Prince:</strong> The scoundrals are asked by a ghost to help put him to rest. <em>The Black Prince pg 177 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li><strong>A Toast to Death:</strong> The scoundrals are tasked with smuggling wine to on of the princes. Unknown to them the wine is poisoned. <em>A Toast to Death pg 173 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n<li>sadfsdf</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Encounters</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Night Swimmers:</strong> During the evening the ship is attacked by a group of Sahuaghin. <em>Event 6 include from Piracy on the Fever Sea from Raiders of the Fever Sea</em></li>\n<li><strong>Wreck of the Carcanus:</strong> Use as a idea for the scounrals aquiring magical sails for their ship. <em>Wreck of Carcanus pg 150 from 50 Fathoms Explorer</em></li>\n</ul>\n</div>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kum3o0fx46","path":"Pirates of Cyre","color":"#008000"}},"_id":"YiBz5OT1eOZeytLS"}
{"name":"Session 0","content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Session 0</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<h2>Campaign Summary</h2>\n<p>Your journey has taken you to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Regalport]{Regalport} in the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Lhazaar Principalities]{Lhazaar Principalities}. You all have come here for different reasons. But each of you find yourselves at an inn called @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.The Salty Dog and The Baron]{the Salty Dog and the Baron}. The night that followed with much drinking, gambling and sea shanties. Or so you think. You wake in the morning, not remembering much after a certain point. You find yourselves in the hold of a ship out at sea. You are press-ganged, and forced to join the crew of the Wormwood, captained by the despicable Berrigan \"Black Red\" Redecker. The main captain at sea for Mika Rockface and the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Cloudreaver Principality]{Cloudreaver Principality}.</p>\n<p>From here you can expect the following to happen over the course of the campaign arc.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You can expect to find your freedom from Black Red.</li>\n<li>You will find yourself in control of your own ship, through mutiny or other means. With you in control how you go about your piracy and time in the sea lanes is up to you.</li>\n<li>Having found your vessel through less than legal means, you must find a way to disguise the ship and hide the means of identifying it's origins.</li>\n<li>Onto piracy.</li>\n<li>Fighting some other pirates can lead to treasure maps. Or maybe it comes time to claim a base of operations to store plunder, repair your ship, and hide from prying eyes.</li>\n</ol>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":null,"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"monks-enhanced-journal":{},"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_kum3o0fx46","path":"Pirates of Cyre","color":"#008000"}},"_id":"bDPhr71fnG34Cndy"}
